    "We find the following factorized formII 4d SO(2N + 1) D ′ (t, x i = q i 2 t -2i; q) = N k=1 (q k+ 1 2 t -4k+2; q) ∞ (q k t -4k; q) ∞ × I 3d tHM (x = q 1 4 t -1) N × N -1 l=1 I 3d tHM (x = q 4l-1 4 t -4l+1) N -l × N -1 m=1 I 3d tHM (x = q 4m+1 4 t -4m-1) N -m. (3.15)By stripping off the full-indices of the 3d twisted hypermultiplets which will be decoupled along the RG-flow, we get the half-index of the regular Nahm pole boundary condition for N = 4 SO(2N + 1) gauge theory II 4d SO(2N + 1) Nahm ′ (t; q) = N k=1 (q k+ 1 2 t -4k+2; q) ∞ (q k t -4k; q) ∞.",
    "(3I SO(2N +1) 1 2 BPS (q) = I USp(2N) 1 2 BPS (q) = N n=1 1 1 -q 4n.",
